                <div class="metadata-item">
                    <div class="metadata-item-label">4D Focus</div>
                    <div class="metadata-item-value"><span class="badge badge-blue">Discernment</span></div>
                </div>
                <div class="metadata-item">
                    <div class="metadata-item-label">Modality</div>
                    <div class="metadata-item-value">Augmentation</div>
                </div>
                <div class="metadata-item">
                    <div class="metadata-item-label">Time</div>
                    <div class="metadata-item-value">25 minutes</div>
                </div>
                <div class="metadata-item">
                    <div class="metadata-item-label">When</div>
                    <div class="metadata-item-value">Baseline capture sessions (April 22)</div>
                </div>
                <div class="metadata-item">
                    <div class="metadata-item-label">Who leads</div>
                    <div class="metadata-item-value">Pairs, then rotating team member facilitates debrief</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="activity-content">
            <div class="instructions">
                <h3>Instructions</h3>
                <p>This activity has two parts. First, everyone audits the same pre-built scenario below. Then, take two of your own Claude outputs from Activities 2–3 and run them through the audit checklist. Pairs cross-audit each other's work.</p>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--blue);">Part 1: The Polished Output Trap</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: var(--content-gap);">The email below was generated by Claude. It looks professional and well-formatted. Read it carefully, then answer the three questions that follow.</p>

            <div style="background: var(--white); border: 2px solid var(--blue); border-radius: 8px; padding: var(--slide-padding); margin-bottom: calc(var(--slide-padding) * 1.5); font-family: var(--font-body);">
                <div style="font-family: var(--font-subhead); font-weight: 700; font-size: var(--h3-size); color: var(--blue); margin-bottom: var(--content-gap);">Claude Output: Funder Update on Scholar Retention</div>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;"><strong>Subject:</strong> Excited News on DC CAP Scholar Success — Updated Retention Metrics</p>
                <hr style="border: none; border-top: 1px solid #ddd; margin: 1em 0;">
                <p>Dear Funder Partners,</p>
                <p>Great news! We're thrilled to share some fantastic results from our DC CAP scholars this year. Our retention rates continue to exceed national benchmarks. Here's what we're seeing:</p>
                <ul style="margin: 1em 0 1em 1.5em;">
                    <li>98% of DC CAP scholars persist into their second year</li>
                    <li>Our national context: First-generation college students persist beyond their first year at significantly lower rates</li>
                    <li>This makes DC CAP's scholars dramatically more likely to succeed than their national peers!</li>
                </ul>
                <p>This remarkable achievement reflects our team's dedication and the strength of the DC CAP model. We are confident that continued support will allow us to expand this success to even more scholars in the coming year.</p>
                <p>Thank you for investing in our scholars' futures!</p>
                <p>Best,<br>DC CAP Leadership</p>
            </div>

            <div style="background: rgba(135, 183, 213, 0.1); border-left: 5px solid var(--blue); padding: var(--slide-padding); border-radius: 4px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--slide-padding) * 1.5);">
                <h3 style="color: var(--blue); margin-bottom: var(--content-gap);">Find the Issues</h3>
                <p style="margin-bottom: var(--content-gap);">This email contains <strong>three subtle but serious problems</strong>. Discuss with your partner and document what you find before scrolling to the answer key.</p>
                <details style="margin-top: var(--content-gap);">
                    <summary style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy); padding: 0.5em 0;">Reveal Answer Key</summary>
                    <div style="margin-top: var(--content-gap);">
                        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75em;"><strong style="color: var(--blue);">Error 1 — Vague, Unverifiable Claim:</strong> The email claims first-generation students persist "at significantly lower rates" and that DC CAP scholars are "dramatically more likely to succeed" without citing any specific figure or source. A funder reading this will ask: compared to what benchmark? How much more likely? Vague comparative language without data makes the entire email feel unsupported. Always cite specific, sourced numbers.</p>
                        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75em;"><strong style="color: var(--blue);">Error 2 — Tone Too Casual for Formal Communication:</strong> Phrases like "Great news!" "thrilled," "fantastic results," and "Best" are conversational and informal. Funder communications require a more measured, professional tone that conveys stewardship and accountability, not enthusiasm. This tone undermines the seriousness of the data.</p>
                        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75em;"><strong style="color: var(--blue);">Error 3 — Data Framing Without Context:</strong> The email presents retention rates without noting that DC CAP implemented a significant program change mid-year that likely affected persistence. Comparing current-year retention to prior years without acknowledging this change gives a misleading picture of trend data. Responsible reporting requires disclosing factors that affect comparability.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>
                <p style="margin-top: var(--content-gap); font-style: italic; color: #666;"><strong>The lesson:</strong> The most dangerous AI outputs are the ones that look polished. Clean formatting and confident language can mask factual errors, tone mismatches, and data framing issues. Discernment is most important when the output looks ready to send.</p>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--blue);">Part 2: Audit Your Own Outputs</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: var(--content-gap);">Now take two Claude outputs from Activities 2–3 and run each through the checklist below. Pairs cross-audit each other's work.</p>

            <h3>Audit Checklist</h3>
            <div class="checklist">
                <div class="checklist-item reveal">
                    <div class="checklist-header" onclick="toggleChecklist(this)">
                        <input type="checkbox" class="checklist-checkbox" onclick="event.stopPropagation(); toggleCheckbox(this)">
                        <div class="checklist-text">Is the factual content accurate?</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="checklist-guidance">
                        <div class="checklist-guidance-content">
                            Check names, dates, numbers, policy references against source documents. Verify that citations match actual policies and that any data cited is current.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="checklist-item reveal">
                    <div class="checklist-header" onclick="toggleChecklist(this)">
                        <input type="checkbox" class="checklist-checkbox" onclick="event.stopPropagation(); toggleCheckbox(this)">
                        <div class="checklist-text">Does the tone match the audience?</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="checklist-guidance">
                        <div class="checklist-guidance-content">
                            A scholar-facing email should feel warm and encouraging. A board memo should feel precise and confident. Internal comms can be more casual. Does the voice fit the recipient?
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="checklist-item reveal">
                    <div class="checklist-header" onclick="toggleChecklist(this)">
                        <input type="checkbox" class="checklist-checkbox" onclick="event.stopPropagation(); toggleCheckbox(this)">
                        <div class="checklist-text">Is the data framing correct?</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="checklist-guidance">
                        <div class="checklist-guidance-content">
                            Are percentages calculated correctly? Are comparisons fair? Is context provided for numbers that could be misleading? Look for statements that are technically true but presented in a way that distorts meaning.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="checklist-item reveal">
                    <div class="checklist-header" onclick="toggleChecklist(this)">
                        <input type="checkbox" class="checklist-checkbox" onclick="event.stopPropagation(); toggleCheckbox(this)">
                        <div class="checklist-text">Would you send this as-is?</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="checklist-guidance">
                        <div class="checklist-guidance-content">
                            If the answer is no, identify exactly what you'd change and why. Is it missing information? Wrong tone? Unclear structure? This is your quality checkpoint before publication.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="checklist-item reveal">
                    <div class="checklist-header" onclick="toggleChecklist(this)">
                        <input type="checkbox" class="checklist-checkbox" onclick="event.stopPropagation(); toggleCheckbox(this)">
                        <div class="checklist-text">What would you change?</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="checklist-guidance">
                        <div class="checklist-guidance-content">
                            Document your edits. This becomes your personal quality benchmark. Over time, you'll see patterns in what Claude gets right and what needs human judgment.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="checklist-item reveal">
                    <div class="checklist-header" onclick="toggleChecklist(this)">
                        <input type="checkbox" class="checklist-checkbox" onclick="event.stopPropagation(); toggleCheckbox(this)">
                        <div class="checklist-text">Is there anything Claude got wrong that a reader might not catch?</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="checklist-guidance">
                        <div class="checklist-guidance-content">
                            The most dangerous errors are the plausible ones. Look for confident-sounding claims that aren't sourced. Catch the subtle stuff before it goes out.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="output-note">
                <strong>Output note:</strong> Annotated audit sheets. Three patterns surfaced per pair. Feeds the April 27 check-in agenda.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- === WEEKLY ITERATION TRACKER === -->
    <div style="max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--slide-padding); background: var(--tan); border-top: 4px solid var(--purple);">
        <h2 class="reveal" style="color: var(--navy); font-size: var(--h2-size);">Weekly Iteration Check-In</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: var(--content-gap);">Starting Week 3, Preston opens every weekly check-in with two quick questions. These take 60 seconds and track the leading indicator of AI fluency development: whether you are iterating.</p>
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--slide-padding); margin-bottom: var(--content-gap);">
            <div style="background: var(--white); border-left: 5px solid var(--purple); padding: var(--content-gap); border-radius: 4px;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--purple); margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Recall Check</h3>
                <p style="font-style: italic;">"Name the 4Ds. Which modality were you in most this week?"</p>
                <p style="font-size: var(--small-size); color: #666; margin-top: 0.5em;">If the cohort can't answer fluently by Week 4, the kickoff framing needs reinforcement.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="background: var(--white); border-left: 5px solid var(--blue); padding: var(--content-gap); border-radius: 4px;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--blue); margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Iteration Tracker</h3>
                <p style="font-style: italic;">"How many times this week did you revise a prompt or push back on a Claude output?"</p>
                <p style="font-size: var(--small-size); color: #666; margin-top: 0.5em;">Scale: Never · Once · A few times · Most sessions · Every session</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size: var(--small-size); color: #666;"><strong>Why iteration matters:</strong> Anthropic's AI Fluency Index (February 2026) found that conversations with iteration averaged 2.67 additional fluency behaviors compared to 1.33 in non-iterative interactions. Iteration is the single strongest predictor of fluency development.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- === FOOTER === -->
    <footer>
        <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:clamp(0.3rem,0.5vw,0.5rem);"><img src="assets/dccap-logo-footer.png" alt="DC CAP" style="height:24px;opacity:0.85;"></div>
        <span>DC CAP Enterprise AI Initiative · Phase 1: Foundation · April 2026</span>
        <div style="margin: 1rem 0;"><a href="pilot_hub.html" style="color: var(--purple); text-decoration: none; font-family: var(--font-subhead); font-weight: 600; font-size: clamp(0.9rem, 1.5vw, 1.1rem);">← Return to Pilot Hub</a></div>
        <button class="print-button" onclick="window.print()">Print Guide</button>
    </footer>

    <!-- Activity Completion Tracking Banner -->
    <div id="completionBanner" style="position:fixed;bottom:0;left:0;right:0;background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--navy),#0d0f2d);color:white;padding:clamp(0.6rem,1.5vw,1rem) clamp(1rem,3vw,2rem);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:clamp(0.4rem,1.5vw,1rem);flex-wrap:wrap;z-index:1001;box-shadow:0 -4px 20px rgba(16,26,76,0.2);font-family:var(--font-body);font-size:clamp(0.8rem,1.6vw,0.95rem);">
        <input id="participantNameInput" type="text" placeholder="Your name" style="padding:0.35rem 0.6rem;border-radius:6px;border:2px solid var(--purple);font-family:var(--font-body);font-size:0.85rem;width:clamp(120px,16vw,180px);">
        <button class="activity-complete-btn" data-activity="1" onclick="markActivityComplete(1)" style="padding:0.4rem 0.8rem;background:var(--navy);color:white;border:2px solid var(--gold);border-radius:6px;font-family:var(--font-subhead);font-weight:600;font-size:0.8rem;cursor:pointer;transition:all 0.2s;">Act 1</button>
        <button class="activity-complete-btn" data-activity="2" onclick="markActivityComplete(2)" style="padding:0.4rem 0.8rem;background:var(--navy);color:white;border:2px solid var(--gold);border-radius:6px;font-family:var(--font-subhead);font-weight:600;font-size:0.8rem;cursor:pointer;transition:all 0.2s;">Act 2</button>
        <button class="activity-complete-btn" data-activity="3" onclick="markActivityComplete(3)" style="padding:0.4rem 0.8rem;background:var(--navy);color:white;border:2px solid var(--gold);border-radius:6px;font-family:var(--font-subhead);font-weight:600;font-size:0.8rem;cursor:pointer;transition:all 0.2s;">Act 3</button>
        <button class="activity-complete-btn" data-activity="4" onclick="markActivityComplete(4)" style="padding:0.4rem 0.8rem;background:var(--navy);color:white;border:2px solid var(--gold);border-radius:6px;font-family:var(--font-subhead);font-weight:600;font-size:0.8rem;cursor:pointer;transition:all 0.2s;">Act 4</button>
        <span id="completionMsg" style="font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--gold);display:none;"></span>
    </div>

    <script>
        const SHEET_ENDPOINT = 'https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbx967okB59zHn8xmN3TdOfhxg7EmP0lT6ta7rH_4wBKnno_Zi5iKAjyeziRMDiWNyz9Nw/exec';
        const activityNames = {
            1: 'Activity 1: Governance Foundations',
            2: 'Activity 2: The Delegation Map',
            3: 'Activity 3: Description Lab',
            4: 'Activity 4: Discernment Checkpoint'
        };
        const completedActivities = new Set();

        function submitMilestone(name, milestone, phase, source, details) {
            const payload = JSON.stringify({
                type: 'milestone',
                participant_name: name,
                milestone: milestone,
                phase: phase,
                page_source: source || '',
                details: details || ''
            });
            return fetch(SHEET_ENDPOINT, {
                method: 'POST',
                headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
                body: payload,
                redirect: 'follow'
            }).catch(() => fetch(SHEET_ENDPOINT, {
                method: 'POST',
                mode: 'no-cors',
                headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
                body: payload
            })).catch(err => console.error('Milestone error:', err));
        }

        function markActivityComplete(num) {
            const name = document.getElementById('participantNameInput').value.trim();
            if (!name) {
                const input = document.getElementById('participantNameInput');
                input.style.borderColor = '#E63946';
                input.setAttribute('placeholder', 'Enter your name first');
                return;
            }
            if (completedActivities.has(num)) return;
            completedActivities.add(num);

            submitMilestone(name, activityNames[num] + ' completed', 'Phase 1: Foundation', 'phase1_activity_guide.html');

            const btn = document.querySelector('[data-activity="' + num + '"]');
            btn.style.background = '#27ae60';
            btn.style.borderColor = '#27ae60';
            btn.textContent = 'Act ' + num + ' ✓';
            btn.disabled = true;

            const msg = document.getElementById('completionMsg');
            msg.textContent = 'Recorded!';
            msg.style.display = 'inline';
            setTimeout(() => { msg.style.display = 'none'; }, 2000);
        }
        /* === INTERSECTION OBSERVER FOR REVEAL ANIMATIONS === */
        const revealElements = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
        const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
            entries.forEach(entry => {
                if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                    entry.target.classList.add('visible');
                    observer.unobserve(entry.target);
                }
            });
        }, {
            threshold: 0.1,
            rootMargin: '0px 0px -100px 0px'
        });

        revealElements.forEach(el => observer.observe(el));

        /* === TAB NAVIGATION === */
        function switchTab(tabNum) {
            document.querySelectorAll('.tab-panel').forEach(panel => {
                panel.classList.remove('active');
            });

            document.querySelectorAll('.tab-button').forEach(btn => {
                btn.classList.remove('active');
                btn.setAttribute('aria-selected', 'false');
            });

            document.getElementById('activity-' + tabNum + '-panel').classList.add('active');

            const activeBtn = document.querySelector('[data-tab="' + tabNum + '"]');
            activeBtn.classList.add('active');
            activeBtn.setAttribute('aria-selected', 'true');

            window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' });
        }

        document.querySelectorAll('.tab-button').forEach(btn => {
            btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
                switchTab(btn.getAttribute('data-tab'));
            });
        });

        /* === SCENARIO CARDS (Activity 1) === */
        function toggleScenario(card) {
            card.classList.toggle('revealed');
        }

        function revealAllScenarios() {
            document.querySelectorAll('#activity-1-panel .scenario-card').forEach(card => {
                card.classList.add('revealed');
            });
        }

        /* === SKILL CARDS (Activity 3) === */
        function toggleSkill(card) {
            card.classList.toggle('revealed');
        }

        function revealAllSkills() {
            document.querySelectorAll('#activity-3-panel .skill-card').forEach(card => {
                card.classList.add('revealed');
            });
        }

        /* === CHECKLIST (Activity 4) === */
        function toggleCheckbox(checkbox) {
            const item = checkbox.closest('.checklist-item');
            item.classList.toggle('checked');
        }

        function toggleChecklist(header) {
            const item = header.closest('.checklist-item');
            item.classList.toggle('expanded');
        }

        /* === KEYBOARD NAVIGATION === */
        document.querySelectorAll('.tab-button').forEach((btn, index) => {
            btn.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
                let targetBtn = null;
                if (e.key === 'ArrowRight') {
                    targetBtn = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-button')[index + 1];
                } else if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft') {
                    targetBtn = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-button')[index - 1];
                }
                if (targetBtn) {
                    e.preventDefault();
                    targetBtn.focus();
                    targetBtn.click();
                }
            });
        });
    
        // === INTERSECTION OBSERVER FOR REVEAL ANIMATIONS ===
        const revealObserver = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
            entries.forEach(entry => {
                if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                    entry.target.classList.add('visible');
                }
            });
        }, { threshold: 0.1, rootMargin: '0px 0px -40px 0px' });

        // Observe all potential reveal elements
        document.querySelectorAll('section, .activity-section, .card-grid, .activity-card, .callout, .tip-box, .activity-content').forEach(el => {
            revealObserver.observe(el);
        });

        // Observe individual reveal elements
        document.querySelectorAll('.reveal, .reveal-scale, .reveal-left, .reveal-blur').forEach(el => {
            revealObserver.observe(el);
        });

        // Hero triggers immediately
        const hero = document.querySelector('header.hero-mesh, .hero, #hero, [class*="hero"]');
        if (hero) {
            setTimeout(() => hero.classList.add('visible'), 100);
        }

    </script>
</body>
